The paper discusses the recovery of a structured signal from random linear measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of convex programming and empirical process theory suggests a focus on optimization and statistical learning, which further supports these categories.
